# Afya Links: Pharmacy Payout & Supply Match Updates

This plan covers the implementation of the new business rules requested for the pharmacy payout logic, the new preferred supply area matching, and SMS sender ID defaults.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Are the `preferred_supply_towns` and `supply_areas` meant to be simple comma-separated strings or arrays of strings? For this MVP, I plan to store them as `TEXT[]` arrays in the database to allow multiple area selections easily.
> - For SMS, the code `at.SMS.send({ to, message })` already omits a `from` key, meaning Africa's Talking defaults to the shared origin. This appears to be correct out-of-the-box unless there's another place SMS gets triggered?

## Proposed Changes

### Database Migrations
We will create a new SQL migration file (`supabase/06_pharmacy_payouts_and_supply.sql`) covering:
- **`pharmacy_wallet` table**: `pharmacy_id`, `available_balance`, `lifetime_payouts`, `updated_at`.
- **`payout_requests` table**: `id`, `pharmacy_id`, `amount`, `payment_method`, `payment_details` (JSON), `status` (PENDING/PAID/REJECTED), `created_at`.
- **`clinic_profiles` table alterations**: Add `preferred_supply_towns` `TEXT[]`.
- **`pharmacy_profiles` table alterations**: Add `supply_areas` `TEXT[]`, `preferred_payout_method` `VARCHAR`, `payout_details` `JSONB`.

---

### Backend Components

#### [MODIFY] [backend/src/controllers/payment.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/Fix/Desktop/Afya%20Links/backend/src/controllers/payment.controller.ts)
- In [confirmPaymentByTrackingId](file:///c:/Users/Fix/Desktop/Afya%20Links/backend/src/controllers/payment.controller.ts#10-107): After successful status update to `PAID`, fetch the calculated `platform_commission` on the order and compute the pharmacy earnings.
- Upsert to `pharmacy_wallet` using an RPC call or direct update to increment `available_balance`.

#### [NEW] `backend/src/controllers/payout.controller.ts`
- `requestPayout`: Pharmacy endpoint. Validates `$balance >= 500_000` UGX, checks for 24-hour cooldown using `created_at` of last request, deducts balance, inserts a `PENDING` request, and emails admin.
- `getPayoutHistory`: Pharmacy endpoint. Fetches their past payout requests.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/src/routes/pharmacyRoutes.ts`
- Add routes for `GET /wallet`, `POST /payout`, `GET /payouts`.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/src/controllers/admin.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/Fix/Desktop/Afya%20Links/backend/src/controllers/admin.controller.ts)
- Add `getPayoutRequests`: Returns all requests, grouping high balance alerts (Level 1: >= 500k, Level 2: >= 1m).
- Add `markPayoutPaid`: Admin endpoint to update `payout_requests` to `PAID`, generating a simulated invoice/history entry.

#### [MODIFY] `backend/src/routes/adminRoutes.ts`
- Add `/payouts` and `/payouts/:id/pay` endpoints.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/src/controllers/clinic.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/Fix/Desktop/Afya%20Links/backend/src/controllers/clinic.controller.ts) & [pharmacy.controller.ts](file:///c:/Users/Fix/Desktop/Afya%20Links/backend/src/controllers/pharmacy.controller.ts)
- **Profile Updates**: Allow submitting `preferred_supply_towns` (for clinics) and `supply_areas` / `preferred_payout_method` / `payout_details` (for pharmacies).
- **Matching Logic**: Update the pharmacy listing endpoint (used by clinics) to fetch pharmacies where there's an intersection between `clinic.preferred_supply_towns` and `pharmacy.supply_areas`.

#### [MODIFY] [backend/src/utils/sms.ts](file:///c:/Users/Fix/Desktop/Afya%20Links/backend/src/utils/sms.ts)
- Confirm removal of any hardcoded Sender ID to ensure fallback to Africa's Talking shared sender.

